definitions.definition: ( transitive , nautical ) To run aground ; to beach.
( transitive , figuratively ) To leave (someone) in a difficult situation; to abandon or desert .
( transitive , baseball ) To cause the third out of an inning to be made, leaving a runner on base.
examples: Jones pops up; that's going to strand a pair.

definitions.definition: ( transitive , grammar ) To leave an element (e.g., an adposition ) without its complement adjacent to it.

definitions.definition: To break a strand of (a rope).

main_definition: ( transitive ) To break a strand of (a rope).
secondary_definitions: ( transitive ) To form by uniting strands.
